title: Slow Cooker Chicken and Dumplings
directions: Place the chicken, butter, soup, and onion in a slow cooker, and fill with enough water to cover. Watch Now
Cover, and cook for 5 to 6 hours on High. About 30 minutes before serving, place the torn biscuit dough in the slow cooker. Cook until the dough is no longer raw in the center. Watch Now
ingredients: 2 (10.75 ounce) cans condensed cream of chicken soup
2 (10 ounce) packages refrigerated biscuit dough, torn into pieces
